Create a class in Java to represent a student and implement methods to compare two student objects.

### Response:
public class Student {
    private String name;
    private int age;

    public Student(String name, int age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }

    public boolean isYoungerThan(Student otherStudent) {
        return this.age < otherStudent.getAge();
    }

    public boolean isOlderThan(Student otherStudent) {
        return this.age > otherStudent.getAge();
    }

