### Instruction:
Create a function in Java which can take an array of any type and sort it in ascending order.

### Response:
public static<T extends Comparable<T>> void sort (T[] arr)
{
    T temp;
    for (int i = 0; i < arr.length-1; i++)
    {
        for (int j = i+1; j < arr.length; j++)
        {
            if (arr[i].compareTo(arr[j]) > 0)
            {
                temp = arr[i];
                arr[i] = arr[j];
                arr[j] = temp;
            }
        }
    }
}

